@startuml
actor Client
participant "Service Provider" as SP #D3D3F0
database "Authorization Provider\n(Identity Server)" as AuthServer #E6E6FA

Client ->> AuthServer : POST /register \n(client_id, client_secret) 
AuthServer --> Client : 201 Created 

note right of Client: Store credentials securely in config file or environment variables


group Token Request & Response
    note over Client,SP: Use stored credentials to request access token
    
    activate Client
        Client->>AuthServer:POST/token(grant_type=client_credentials&\nscope=read+write)\n(Authorization header contains Basic auth string from base64 encoded <b>"<u><i>{clientId}:{secret}</i></u>\n"</b>)  
        
